      The fines, settlements, and remediation costs that fill the headline are typically less than ten per cent of the total damage. Eleven-twelfths of the cost arrives after the disclosure event &mdash; through share-price decline, credit downgrade, funding-cost increase, and customer attrition that compound rather than merely add. The cascade is the empirical signature of governance failure&rsquo;s persistence. It is also the reason the time from risk crystallisation to board awareness is the single most important variable governance can affect.
    </p>
